  <h2>Favorite Senior Portrait Locations in Hartland</h2>

  <h3>Parshallville</h3>
  <p>The historic Parshallville Cider Mill area is one of the most photogenic spots in all of Livingston County. The old stone bridge, the creek, the rustic mill buildings — it's pure Michigan charm. In fall, the surrounding trees put on an incredible show.</p>

  <h3>Local Farms &amp; Open Fields</h3>
  <p>Hartland's countryside is dotted with beautiful farms, horse pastures, and wildflower meadows. If your family has property in the area, shooting on your own land adds a personal connection that studio photos could never capture. Some of my most memorable sessions have happened on Hartland family farms.</p>

  <h3>Hartland Music Hall Area</h3>
  <p>The historic downtown area around the Hartland Music Hall has that authentic small-town feel — wooden facades, quiet streets, and great natural light in the late afternoon.</p>

  <h3>Ore Creek &amp; Trail Systems</h3>
  <p>For seniors who want a more natural, adventurous feel, the trails and creek areas around Hartland offer wooded paths, water features, and a sense of being tucked away in nature while still being 5 minutes from town.</p>

  <h2>What Your Session Looks Like</h2>
  <p>We start with a consultation to plan outfits, locations, and timing. On session day, I guide you through natural poses and movements — no stiffness, no awkward silence. Golden hour sessions are my specialty. Most sessions include 2-3 outfit changes and last about 90 minutes.</p>

